hints_latex:
For a continuous random variable \emph{X} with probability density
function \emph{f(x)} the probability that an event \emph{a} $\leq$
\emph{X} $\leq$ \emph{b} happens is

\begin{align*}
\text{Prob}(a \leq X \leq b) = \int_a^b f(x)\,dx.
\end{align*}

